-- Colombian Stocks: Isagen, Pacific Rubiales Energy Were Active
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-04-20T21:17:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-20/colombian-stocks-isagen-pacific-rubiales-energy-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  rose 0.1 percent to 15,016.67, while the
Colcap Index increased 0.2 percent to 1,754.56.  Isagen SA (ISAGEN)  , a Colombian energy company, advanced
2.3 percent to 2,400 pesos, extending its gain this week to 6.2
percent. Investors are buying shares before April 23, after
which holders won’t receive the right to a dividend payment,
said Juan Camilo Martinez, an analyst at Medellin-based
brokerage Bolsa y Renta. Isagen will pay a 77 peso per share
dividend payment on April 27, according to a  filing  March 27 to
the financial regulator’s website.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , the Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in  Colombia , climbed 1.4
percent to 51,600 pesos. Pacific Rubiales gained as oil rose for
the first time in three days.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christine Jenkins in New York at 
